<html><head></head><body><b>Kirchhoff's First Law</b><br/>A point in a circuit where <br/>at least three connections <br/>to different conductors meet is called a junction. The sum of the currents flowing into <br/>a given junction is equal <br/>to the sum of currents flowing out of that junction. This statement is known <br/>as Kirchhoff's First Law.</body></html>